Datasets of compound biomarkers - omics properties that are linked to drug response

Source: R/data.R
compound_biomarkers.Rd

Datasets of compound biomarkers - omics properties that are linked to drug response

compound_biomarkers

Format

curated - A data frame with 235,340 rows and 26 columns:

  • evidence_id - evidence identifier

  • evidence_url - evidence URL

  • variant_id - variant identifier

  • variant_type - type of variant

  • variant - variant (alias)

  • alteration_type - type of genetic alteration

  • symbol - drug target (gene symbol)

  • therapeutic_context - therapeutic context (drug sensitivity/resistance)

  • disease_ontology_id - disease ontology (DO) identifier (mapped - oncoPhenoMap)

  • cancer_type - tumor type/disease (provided by source)

  • molecule_chembl_id - ChEMBL compound identifier

  • citation_id - citation identifier (PMID etc)

  • evidence_description - evidence description

  • evidence_type - evidence type

  • evidence_level - evidence level

  • evidence_direction - evidence direction

  • clinical_significance - clinical significance

  • variant_origin - variant origin (somatic/germline)

  • biomarker_source_db - type of biomarker source database

  • biomarker_entity - logical indicating biomarker entity

  • efo_id - EFO identifier (mapped - oncoPhenoMap)

  • efo_name - EFO name (mapped - oncoPhenoMap)

  • do_name - disease ontology (DO) name (mapped - oncoPhenoMap)

  • cui - disease UMLS identifier (mapped - oncoPhenoMap)

  • cui_name - disease UMLS name (mapped - oncoPhenoMap)

  • primary_site - primary tumor site (mapped - oncoPhenoMap)

invitro_screen - A data frame with 10,182 rows and 8 columns:

  • compound_id - compound identifier (PRISM)

  • model - type of omics drug prediction model (DepMap/PRISM)

  • feature_type - type of omics feature

  • feature_value - value of omics feature

  • feature_importance - omics feature importance

  • prediction_accuracy - model prediction accuracy

  • nci_concept_display_name - Primary drug name (NCI Thesaurus)

  • molecule_chembl_id - ChEMBL compound identifier

Source

https://civicdb.org/

https://www.cancergenomeinterpreter.org/biomarkers

https://pmkb.weill.cornell.edu/

https://mitelmandatabase.isb-cgc.org/

https://depmap.org/portal/
